    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="896"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d896">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 850a.001/6.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6, Luxemburg series.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith, together
                    with the office copy thereof, a letter<note n="1" xml:id="d896fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> addressed to the President of the United <pb facs="0819"
                        n="703" xml:id="pg_703"/> States of America, which I have this day received
                    from the Minister of State, President of the Government of the Grand Duchy of
                    Luxemburg, whereby her Royal Highness the Grand Duchess, Regent of the Grand
                    Duchy, notifies the President of the United States of the decease of His Royal
                    Highness the Grand Duke William, and of the continuance of the Regency until the
                    attainment of majority of Her Royal Highness the Grand Duchess Marie
                    Adelaide.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lloyd Bryce.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
